Class Configuration

      • getFullProperties

        public Map<String,Map<String,String>> getFullProperties()
        Get a complete merged map of properties including this instance and the entire parent hierarchy. Properties are merged so that children override the same property specified in it's parent hierarchy. This result is re-calculated for each request in case a parent value has changed so the result should be cached if possible.
        Returns:
        complete map of merged properties keyed by config type

      • getFullProperties

        public Map<String,Map<String,String>> getFullProperties(int depthLimit)
        Get a merged map of properties including this instance and n levels of the parent hierarchy. Properties are merged so that children override the same property specified in it's parent hierarchy. This result is re-calculated for each request in case a parent value has changed so the result should be cached if possible.
        Parameters:
        depthLimit - the number of parent levels to include in the results. Specifying 0 is the same as calling getProperties()
        Returns:
        map of merged properties keyed by config type

      • getAttributes

        public Map<String,Map<String,Map<String,String>>> getAttributes()
        Get the attributes for this instance only; parent attributes aren't included.
        Returns:
        map of attributes {configType -> {attributeName -> {propName, attributeValue}}}

      • getFullAttributes

        public Map<String,Map<String,Map<String,String>>> getFullAttributes()
        Get a complete merged map of attributes including this instance and the entire parent hierarchy. Attributes are merged so that children override the same attribute specified in it's parent hierarchy. This result is re-calculated for each request in case a parent value has changed so the result should be cached if possible.
        Returns:
        complete map of merged attributes {configType -> {attributeName -> {propName, attributeValue}}}

      • setProperty

        public String setProperty(String configType,
                          String propertyName,
                          String value)
        Set a property on the configuration. The property will be set on this instance so it will override any value specified in the parent hierarchy.
        Parameters:
        configType - configuration type
        propertyName - property name
        value - property value
        Returns:
        the previous value of the property or null if it didn't exist

      • removeProperty

        public String removeProperty(String configType,
                             String propertyName)
        Remove a property from the configuration hierarchy. All occurrences of the property are removed from the config hierarchy such that a subsequent call to getPropertyValue() for the removed property will return null.
        Parameters:
        configType - configuration type
        propertyName - property name
        Returns:
        the previous value of the removed property or null if it didn't exist in the configuration hierarchy

      • moveProperties

        public Set<String> moveProperties(String sourceConfigType,
                                  String targetConfigType,
                                  Set<String> propertiesToMove)
        Moves the given properties from sourceConfigType to targetConfigType. If a property is already present in the target, it will be removed from the source, but not overwritten in the target.
        Parameters:
        sourceConfigType - the config type to move properties from
        targetConfigType - the config type to move properties to
        propertiesToMove - names of properties to be moved
        Returns:
        property names that were removed from the source
